body:
Given the following json swagger spec document, the generated server will fails to compile due to invalid generated go code.

``` json
{
  "host": "localhost",
  "schemes": ["https"],
  "swagger": "2.0",
  "produces": ["application/json"],
  "consumes": ["application/json"],
  "info": {
    "title": "Soda Booth",
    "version": "2.0"
  },
  "paths": {
    "/v2/locations/{location_id}/transactions": {
      "get": {
        "summary": "Sodas",
        "tags": ["Sodas"],
        "description": "Lists sodas for a particular location.",
        "parameters": [
          {
            "name": "Authorization",
            "required": true,
            "type": "string",
            "in": "header"
          },
          {
            "name": "location_id",
            "required": true,
            "type": "string",
            "in": "path"
          }
        ],
        "responses": {"200": {
          "schema": {"$ref": "#/definitions/SodaResponse"},
          "description": "Success"
        }},
        "operationId": "List"
      }
    }
  },
  "definitions": {
    "SodaBrand": {
      "description": "",
      "enum": [
        "OTHER_BRAND",
        "PEPSI",
        "COKE",
        "CACTUS_COOLER",
        "JOLT"
      ],
      "type": "string"
    },
    "SodaResponse": {
      "description": "",
      "properties": {
        "soda_brand": {"$ref": "#/definitions/SodaBrand"}
      },
      "type": "object"
    }
  }
}
```

Trying to run the server yields the following errors:

``` bash
$> go run main.go
../../models/soda_brand.go:22: invalid receiver type *SodaBrand (SodaBrand is a pointer type)
../../models/soda_brand.go:39: invalid receiver type SodaBrand (SodaBrand is a pointer type)
../../models/soda_brand.go:42: m.validateSodaBrandEnum undefined (type SodaBrand has no field or method validateSodaBrandEnum)
../../models/soda_brand.go:46: m.validateSodaBrandEnum undefined (type SodaBrand has no field or method validateSodaBrandEnum)
../../models/soda_request.go:46: m.Brand.Validate undefined (type *SodaBrand has no field or method Validate)
../../models/soda_response.go:75: m.SodaBrand.Validate undefined (type *SodaBrand has no field or method Validate)
```

These same errors appear in the generated client models.
